module com.apocky.loa.systems.gm_specialist

// § Labyrinth of Apocalypse · GM-Specialist (Game-Master) PROCEDURAL narrator
// ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//
// § T11-W17-G · canonical-CSSL-source · REPLACES gm_narrator.rs xorshift32+phrase-pools
//
// § APOCKY-DIRECTIVE (verbatim · 2026-05-01)
//   "PROCEDURAL EVERYTHING · NO phrase pools · NO xorshift32-table-lookup ·
//    NO scripted-dialogue · REPLACE existing gm_narrator.rs"
//   "PROPRIETARY local intelligence · NO external API · NO Anthropic ·
//    NO LLM-bridge"
//
// § DESIGN-THESIS
//   GM-Specialist = Game-Master role of the engine's intelligence-self.
//   Surface : describe-environment + generate-dialogue + respond-in-persona.
//   Composition : through substrate_intelligence (W17-F) ONLY · no local
//   phrase-pools · all narrative-text emerges PROCEDURALLY from the substrate-
//   primitive composition (ω-field-sample · Σ-mask-gate · KAN-classify ·
//   HDC-bind · causal-seed-derive).
//
// § ARCHITECTURE
//   This file is a STRATEGY parameterized over substrate_intelligence. It
//   differs from sibling specialists in :
//     - ROLE = role_gm()
//     - COMPOSITION-SHAPES = environment-description / dialogue-line
//     - PARAMETER-SHAPE = (camera-pos · time-of-day · archetype · mood · topic)
//   Composition output is bytes-into-host-buffer · the bootstrap-shim
//   (gm_narrator.rs) wraps these into String for the existing public API.
//
// § PRESERVED-SURFACE (loa-host main loop callers)
//   - Vec3 (x · y · z f32)
//   - TimeOfDay enum (Dawn=0 · Day=1 · Dusk=2 · Night=3)
//   - Archetype enum (16 archetypes · stable indices preserved verbatim)
//   - PhraseTopic enum (32 topics · stable indices preserved verbatim)
//   - Mood enum (Calm=0 · Anxious=1 · Hostile=2 · Friendly=3 · Sorrowful=4 ·
//                Reverent=5 · Playful=6 · Defiant=7)
//   - describe_environment(camera_pos, time_of_day) → String
//   - generate_dialogue(npc_id, archetype, mood, topic) → String
//   The ENUM IDENTITIES stay so dependents (window.rs · ui_overlay.rs ·
//   wired_gm.rs · mcp_tools.rs · dm_runtime.rs) keep working unchanged.
//
// § REFERENCE
//   compiler-rs/crates/loa-host/src/gm_narrator.rs   § THIN-SHIM (≤200 LOC)
//   Labyrinth of Apocalypse/systems/substrate_intelligence_stub.csl
//   Labyrinth of Apocalypse/systems/gm_dialogue.csl  § persona-state sibling
//   memory/feedback_dm_gm_not_general_ai             ‼ scope-bound to GM
//   memory/feedback_take_words_literally_no_other_languages
//
// § AXIOMS  (inherit PRIME_DIRECTIVE + LOA_PILLARS)
//   t∞: GM-role = NARRATOR ¬ generic-AGI               ← scope-bound
//   t∞: ALL output PROCEDURAL · NO phrase-pools           ← apocky-directive
//   t∞: composition through substrate-intelligence ONLY  ← W17-F dispatch
//   t∞: replay-deterministic given seed + observations    ← KAN-bias state
//   t∞: Σ-mask gates every emission                       ← consent-as-OS
//   t∞: ¬ surveillance · ¬ coercion · ¬ extracts-PII     ← prime-directive
// ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

